subject: Add ibm/genesis3 support
commitMessage:
Add ibm/genesis3 support

This adds support for the IBM genesis3 board.
The Linux kernel URL is modified to
https://github.com/9elements/linux.
This is the OpenBMC kernel with a lot of patches adding driver support
for mostly fan & voltage/current regulators, i2c muxes and gpio
expanders. This is currently being upstreamed. The plan is to use the
upstream kernel when that work is done.

The following features are implemented:
- fan control
- enable/disable most voltage/current regulators
- all gpio expanders
- powering the system from G3 to S5 using pwrseqd (a software
  implementation of what is normally done with a CPLD on server
  mainboards). Other power states are WIP.

Signed-off-by: Patrick Rudolph <patrick.rudolph@9elements.com>
Signed-off-by: Arthur Heymans <arthur.heymans@9elements.com>

https://jenkins.openbmc.org/job/ci-openbmc/8486/ : FAILURE

Hey Arthur, thanks for the contribution. A few quick comments:

- This is failing CI due to the .patch files introduced here. We have a "repotest" in CI that verifies no new patches are added in a commit. We're slowly working on getting rid of the existing ones.
- OpenBMC has a fork of linux and u-boot that we carry under our github organization. As long as you are actively working on upstreaming your changes, we should be able to carry them within OpenBMC vs. you creating patches or your own Linux fork. Joel has final say on that.
- In general for reviews, smaller is always better. Be great to see this broken into multiple commits (basic config, u-boot, fans, hwmon, inventory, leds, ...). Same overall content but much easier to review.
We also shouldn't have this custom 'pwrseqd'.  See https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blame/master/meta-layer-guidelines.md#L75
